Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; dry leaves
thoroughly and chop into bite-size pieces. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%oz}.
Trim and quarter @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick
pieces. Gently crush @croutons{1} in their bag.

Grate @Parmesan cheese block{1} on the medium holes of a #box grater{} (or
#microplane{}) over a #medium bowl{}.

Add @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{3%tbsp}, 1 tsp @fry seasoning{1%tbsp} (2 tsp
for 4 servings), and juice from half the lemon to bowl; stir to combine.
Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. (You'll use the rest of
the Fry Seasoning in the next step.)

== Steak & Corn ==

Pat @bavette steak{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all
over with remaining Fry Seasoning, salt, and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

While steak cooks, wrap @corn on the cob{2} in damp paper towels.
Microwave until cooked through and tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Let rest in microwave ~{1%minute}. (Careful! Corn will be hot!) Set aside
until ready to serve.

== Balsamic Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, and crushed croutons.

Drizzle with @balsamic glaze{5%tsp}. Add a large drizzle of @olive oil{} and
juice from remaining lemon wedges. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide steak, corn, and salad between plates in separate sections. Spoon as
much lemon-Parmesan sauce over corn as you like. Serve with any remaining
lemon-Parmesan sauce on the side for dipping.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.